description:
Radiator Mounts (upper) for 82 Diesel Vanagon

This is the upper rubber mount for the stock 82 Diesel Vanagon Radiator (two required per radiator) the price is for one.  There is also a lower rubber mount that is different than the upper one.  Part number is 803121273.  Link below.

&nbsp;

Stablizer Bar Link, Front 93-2003 Eurovan

This is the stabilizer bar link that goes between the front sway bar that is 23.5mm down to the lower control arm.  It comes with the two rubber bushings already installed.  One is required per side, or 2 per van.

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

This is the full length speedometer cable that goes from the driver's side front wheel to the speedometer of a VW Bus.  It will work with all Bus from 68-79.  On the 75-79 Bus they originally had an OXY light that was activated by travelling so many miles.  This required a small box with a lower and upper speedometer cable.  This new cable by passes this box and gives you a one piece cable that will work your speedometer but will no longer turn the OXY light on.  Since the OXY light is just an idiot light and not really needed for anything, why not bypass it.

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

This is the coolant hose that goes between the electric coolant pump, and the cylinder head on the 93-95 2.5l Eurovan.  It is number 15 on the chart.

<a href="https://www.vanagain.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/93-EV-coolant-hoses.jpg">https://www.vanagain.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/93-EV-coolant-hoses.jpg</a>

&nbsp;
